title: For Sale/Trade:  Taurus PT-92 Stainless
postcontent:
Taurus PT-92 Stainless Steel, pre-decocker, one mag, pachmayr grips, asking $275 OBO.

I hate buying a gun off of armslist that has problems the seller didn't tell me about. So here's all the dirt on this gun. The frame and slide is scratched and not in pristine condition. I've probably put about 600 rds through it without proper cleanup. So no, it's not like new. Pre-decocker isn't like a pre-lock Smith and Wesson (which usually means better quality) on the Taurus PT-92, it just means that you don't have a decocking option.I only have one mag for it, which I've abused, so the slide doesn't lock back on the last round anymore. Recently, the gun's been stove-piping. This is usually means a dirty or bad ejector. It's not a chronic issue, but if you don't clean it and shoot a hundred rounds through it, it'll not eject casings properly. That is everything that is wrong with this piece.

So what's good about it? At 15 yds (I'm no expert shooter by any means but...) the sights are reliable and your bullets will shoot where the sights are. It'll eat everything, whether it's match grade Horniday, steel case Tul-Ammo, or hollow points. The gun is SMOOTH with a pristine DA/SA trigger that'll give any revolver a run for its money. No issue pulling the slide back, the gun's well broke-in and cycles buttery smooth. The mag still feeds reliably. 9mm is cheap, readily available, and parts for this gun are easy to find. Did I mention the nice pachmayr grips? That wasn't stock and they look good on the gun. $275 OBO, all trades welcomed. Satisfaction guaranteed or your gun/money back. 

Back in the late 90's Beretta stopped making guns for the Brazilian military and police. Taurus came in, bought out the Beretta factory in Brazil, kept the original machinery, re-hired the previous workers, and told them to do exactly what they were doing. A Beretta without the Beratta price. The only real changes they made to the design was the safety lever, which they put in a place that made more common sense.

title: For Sale/Trade:  This site needs a keyboard hero
location: Behind the keyboard, Kentucky, United States
postcontent:
This site needs a keyboard hero and I'm the dude to do it. I'm sick and tired of the over priced run of the mill guns, the traders who think they are the barter king of the century, and the wanna be pawn stars. I'm tired of logging in to see the same shit over posted day after day, tired of the greeding ground this site has become. If you want to buy at pawn store offers buy a pawn shop, no one is here to sell at those prices. And like wise no one is here to pay store price when we all have a gun shop around the corner to buy from at those prices. To steal a quote from Mr. Jim Jones, the one on here not the cult leader, " If wasrs are worth 800 mine has to be worth 1000" is exactly the mind set that has run this site aground. There is not one dracco worth $1000 Jim. Sorry to use you as an example but you did it to yourself. Just because the next guy gouged doesn't mean you should too or that either of your guns are worth the price you want for them. I would love for someone to offer me more money than my guns are worth but thats just not how it works, or how it should be. Yes there are some rare collectible guns listed a couple times a year that can have a open price tag but if it's not your great grand dads war bring back with the according paperwork, you need to hit the bricks and see what they actually sell for at the gun shop, or look up their web site and then knock off a few more dollars since you know damn good and well your not going to warranty it if something goes wrong. I have every intention to wage web warfare on this site until I see the market we had before the second obama scare. It's just going to get worse before it gets better so it would be in the best interest of the honest guys to start flagging the bull shit before all you see are my rambling posts and the occasional gun for sale. If your flagging me your part of the problem and your exactly the guy I want to piss off. Don't send me emails telling me you agree with me because I've already gotten your emails supporting me in the past and then you low balled me or couldn't be bothered to have the courtesy of sending a no thanks when I made fair offers on your stuff. I just want my rug back.. ya know...man

 The Dude abides
